Argentine Businessmen, Workers to Discuss Raise in Minimum Wage

-- B y   E l i a n a   R a s z e w s k i
-- 
2011-08-25T11:35:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-25/argentine-businessmen-workers-to-discuss-raise-in-minimum-wage.html
Argentina ’s labor ministry called a
meeting for tomorrow with labor union and business leaders to
discuss an increase in the country’s  minimum wage , according to
the  official gazette .  Last year, they agreed a 22.7 percent increase, raising the
wage that benefited 227,000 workers to 1,840 pesos ($440) per
month, according to a statement posted on the presidential
 website . The minimum salary has increased 820 percent since
2002, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eliana Raszewski in  Buenos Aires  at 
 eraszewski@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Joshua Goodman  at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net . 